<br />
Non-level-based requisites:<br />
<br />
1. We're very foul mouthed, especially me =p You cannot take offense to this. Be prepared to be reemed for mistakes.<br />
<br />
2. We recruit you for what you apply for, once you are in, I'm not going to tolerate any switching of mains, unless we are in dire need (which is unlikely the case, although I tell all my people to make clerics, but i get a big firm NO for some reason)<br />
<br />
3. Server Transfers are welcome. But must still apply for a certain amount of time because quite frankly, we don't know who you are. But we do know that if you want to sacrifice going cross-server for an application, that you are dedicated and willing to raid.<br />
<br />
4. Once again and I *stress* this... Active and on average, able to raid 4 - 5 days a week (FULL raid days, not just one here one there)<br />
<br />
5. Must know how to play your class. I don't care if you're a cleric with 5 billion AA, and level 65 with FT500 or whatever. If you can't follow CH orders, or know how to heal in a raid situation, we don't need you.<br />
<br />
6. Flag requisites: You are now needed to be FULLY elemental flagged. no partials whatsoever.<br />
<br />
7. Keys in POP needed - Key to the lower depths of the Ruins of Lxanvom (Key you get from High Priest Ulthor to get to Bertoxxulous).<br />
<br />
Depending on your situation, there are exceptions to requirements, though they may not be so negotiable. Classes that are higher in demand may/may not get this break.<br />
<br />
*Addendum 2/17- If you are missing flags, don't hesitate to get them from open raids etc. It's much ezier to getem before you start apping (believe me), and watch out for when TMO retro flags, these are fairly uncommon, but rather successful and planned.<br />
<br />
Applicants are to post on the message board, and write an introduction to yourself (level, AA, Flags, Previous guild history), A small essay regarding your class and it's role in a raid situation, and the top 3 reasons a raid fails. <br />
<br />
Oh one more thing... If you get no's on your apps, it doesn't mean we hate (not yet anyways!) it just means we have some concerns about your apps. Whomever votes no on you, you should talk and get stuff straightened out.<br />
<br />
If you are thinking about joining TMO and just happened to read this on a pass-by but think you're not good enough or TMO is too l337 for you? Well you are wrong. As long as you have activity and the will to learn, you will always improve your game. Don't settle for apping for other guilds just because "you don't think you have what it takes" Apply for yourself then figure out if it's right for you or not! I know there are many TMO who talk to me and tell me, "I didn't apply before because I thought I wasn't good enough." Most of those people fit right in and enjoy the high-end raiding guild on Fennin Ro.<br />
<br />
Good luck to you guys on your applications.</font></p>
	
